cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with scheduling algorithms for multi-hop switch networks and discusses network topologies and end-to-end route delay. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the equilibrium and delay properties of the Proportional Scheduler and analyses the large deviations behaviour of the equilibrium distribution. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with scheduling algorithms for distributed networks. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper discusses independent set scheduling on perfect graphs and shows that non-neighbouring queues are statistically independent. 
- cs.PF (Probability and Statistics) is a possible category as the paper discusses the stationary distribution and product form resource pooling in Store-Forward networks.
